8 ounce Fully Cooked Beef Meatballs
1 unit Onion
1 unit Baby Lettuce
1.5 ounce Italian Dressing
2 tablespoon Mayonnaise
1 unit Tomato Paste
1 unit Marinara Sauce
1 unit Chicken Stock Concentrate
1 teaspoon Dried Oregano
1 teaspoon Garlic Powder
½ cup Mozzarella Cheese
2 unit Demi-Baguette
4 ounce Grape Tomatoes
1 unit Croutons
2 teaspoon Cooking Oil
¼ teaspoon Sugar

• Drizzle oil in a hot medium pan.
Add meatballs and cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned all
over, 3-5 minutes. Transfer to a
plate. TIP: While meatballs brown,
move on to the next step!

• Wash and dry produce.
• Finely dice half the onion (all for 4).
Trim and discard root end from
lettuce and thinly slice leaves.
• Mix Italian dressing and
mayonnaise in a small bowl. TIP:
If the meatballs are still browning,
assemble and plate the salad now!

• Lower heat under pan used for
meatballs and drizzle with oil.
Add diced onion and cook, stirring
occasionally, until softened,
2-3 minutes.
• Whisk in 1⁄4 cup water, tomato
paste, marinara, stock
concentrate, oregano, garlic
powder, and 1⁄4 tsp sugar (1⁄2 cup
water and 1⁄2 tsp sugar for 4).
• Add meatballs back to pan with sauce; stir to coat. Remove from heat and
sprinkle with cheese. Cover with lid and set aside to let cheese melt. TIP:
While cheese melts, toast your bread!

• Halve and toast baguettes.
• In a large bowl, toss lettuce,
tomatoes, and croutons (crushing
in the bag with your hands first)
with as much dressing as you like.
• Top bottom baguette halves with
cheesy meatballs and sauce.
Close subs and serve with salad.